{"id":"obed","term":"Obed","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Serving; worshipping. (1.) A son of Boaz and Ruth (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ruth 4:21\">Ruth 4:21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ruth 4:22\">22</a>), and the grandfather of David (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 1:5\">Matt. 1:5</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:34\">1 Chr. 2:34-38</a>.</p>\n<p>(3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:7\">1 Chr. 26:7</a>.</p>\n<p>(4.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 23:1\">2 Chr. 23:1</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ruth 4:21","Ruth 4:22","Matthew 1:5","1 Chronicles 2:34","1 Chronicles 26:7","2 Chronicles 23:1"]}